Deadline for linking Aadhaar with PAN number extended till Dec. 31.
The deadline for linking Aadhaar number with Permanent Income Tax Account Number (PAN number) has been extended till December 31st.
This is the seventh time that the Central Board of Direct Taxes (CBDT) has extended the deadline for PAN-Aadhaar linking.
The central government had already extended this period for 6 months from March 31st to September 30th.
This period has now been extended for another 3 months.
The Unique Identification Authority of India (UIDAI) issues a 12-digit identification number called Aadhaar number to every Indian citizen.
The Income Tax Department issues a 10-digit numerical and letter identification number called the Permanent Income Tax Account Number (PAN) to individuals and companies who pay income tax.
The Central Board of Direct Taxes had issued a notification on July 1, 2017, requiring linking of Aadhaar number with Income Tax Number.
Since then, the deadline for Aadhaar-PAN linking has been extended several times.
Meanwhile, the Supreme Court, which heard a case against issuing Aadhaar cards to citizens, ruled in September last year that the Aadhaar scheme was legal.
The Supreme Court also ruled that Aadhaar number is mandatory for paying income tax.
Meanwhile, it was announced in the Union Budget on July 5 that it will be sufficient to mention the Aadhaar number instead of the PAN number when filing income tax returns.
